  <Language_en_US>
    <Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_BRITISH_REDCOAT888">
      <Text>British Redcoat</Text>
    </Row>
    <Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_BRITISH_REDCOAT888_STRATEGY">
      <Text>The British Redcoat is a British unique unit, similar to the Minuteman, but amphibious. The Redcoat can move through difficult terrain as though it were clear (all tiles cost 1mp per hex) and receives a bonus when fighting in rough terrain.</Text>
    </Row>
    <Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_BRITISH_REDCOAT888_HELP">
      <Text>One of the first gunpowder units of the game. Only the English may build it. This Unit may move through rough ground as though it were flat.  They can load onto Frigates as a cargo unit.</Text>
    </Row>
    <Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_BRITISH_REDCOAT888_PEDIA">
      <Text>Red coat or Redcoat is a historical term used to refer to soldiers of the British Army because of the red uniforms formerly worn by the majority of regiments. From the mid-17th century to the 19th century, the uniform of most British soldiers, (apart from artillery, rifles and light cavalry), included a madder red coat or coatee. From 1873 onwards, the more vivid shade of scarlet was adopted for all ranks, having previously been worn only by officers, sergeants and all ranks of some cavalry regiments - Wikipedia</Text>
    </Row>
  </Language_en_US>
